						<summary>

						<p>Slab set up near the north prākāra inside the gōpura of the Mahālakshmī temple.</p>						

						<p>1489 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is dated in [Śaka] 1411, other details being lost. This badly damaged record mentions Rāmarāja-Viṭṭhala. The inscription is engraved on very rough surface and the letters are indistinct and illegible.</p>						

						</summary>
